T1  - An empirical analysis of the interrelationships among equity markets under changing exchange rate systems
AU  - Bertoneche, Marc L.
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 3
IS  - 4
SP  - 397
EP  - 405
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/12/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(79)90030-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842667990030X
AB  - The purpose of this article is to investigate the interrelationships between seven stock markets (Germany, France, Italy, the Netherlands, Belgium, the United Kingdom and U.S.A.) over the period 1969–1976. The impact of flexible exchange rates on the various correlation coefficients is shown to be rather low. The results show a trend towards higher segmentation between the various stock exchanges, which means larger opportunities for international diversification. Finally the relationships between stock index variations and exchange rate fluctuations are analyzed.
